    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="570"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d570">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/610</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Netherland Chargé</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DBWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">De Beaufort</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 10, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: This Legation has received the
                    request from your Department to facilitate the shipment of five barrels of
                    flour, one case of ham, one case of bacon, one case of lard, and one box from
                    your Department to the United States Minister at The Hague. I have at once
                    cabled about this matter to the Minister of Foreign Affairs, and am today
                    informed that the Netherland Government makes no objection to allow this
                    shipment to go forward on a Netherland vessel and consigned to the Netherland
                    Government. Where repeated large shipments of food for the United States
                    Legation and consular officers prove that the United States authorities are
                    convinced that food is exceedingly scarce in Holland, the Netherland Government
                    trusts that the shipments of food for the Dutch people will be expedited.</p>
                <p>While informing you of the above I remain [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DBWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">W. de Beaufort</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
